transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Yeah, my name's Pat Hogan.

Speaker 1: I just received another order of 10 pills, and this is the third one, and I'm not ordering these.

Speaker 2: Are they got this on automatic fill or something?

Speaker 1: Okay, let me take a look for you.

Speaker 2: I'm sorry, I'm getting a cold here, so bear with me now.

Speaker 1: Yeah, yeah, no, I got you.

Speaker 2: Mr. Patrick Hogan?

Speaker 1: Yes, Hogan, they go G-A-N.

Speaker 2: Yes, yeah.

Speaker 1: So from what I can see here, Dr. Tariq wrote a prescription for Viagra 100 mg, 10 tablets,

Speaker 2: and because it's 10 tablets, it was 30 days in a month, so he wrote it with refills.

Speaker 1: But if you don't need those refills, Mr. Hogan, I can advise the pharmacy to stop the initial 30 days

Speaker 2: for your 10 pills, and then they're going to pause the prescription, I think, up to half a year,

Speaker 1: so you don't get monthly anymore.

Speaker 2: You can just order as needed.

Speaker 1: Yeah, that's what I want to do.

Speaker 2: I don't know why they keep doing this.

Speaker 1: This is the third one.

Speaker 2: It's refilled with the prescription.

Speaker 1: That's what happened because you get 10, so the doctor assumed that you're active,

Speaker 2: so 10, there was 30 days in a month, you're probably running out.

Speaker 1: So usually they try to avoid you to call rush order because most patients are really active.

Speaker 2: But I'm advising the pharmacy that you need to pause and stop the original 30 days,

Speaker 1: and you're going to order as needed, pause half a year.

Speaker 2: And then to lock your price in, you just need to get 10 pills once or twice a year,

Speaker 1: so that locks your deal, the current price market, so you don't pay new market price.

Speaker 2: No, I don't want to. I want to be able to call as needed.

Speaker 1: Yeah, that's why I told the pharmacy to pause.

Speaker 2: Okay, I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Thank you, sir.

Speaker 1: You have a good one. Bye-bye.
